AD | Celebrate @ghdhair’s 20th anniversary with me where you can win you & your bestie a virtual masterclass with ghd Creative Artist & good friend @samantha.cusick (actual hair queen) and myself! Plus the limited edition Hairitage Couture collection!
 
To enter:
✨ follow @ghdhair & me
✨ like this post
✨ comment below tagging your bestie
✨ must be available on May 26th at 6pm BST onwards
 
GOOD LUCK!!! 🙌🏼💗
 
T&C’s:
Only open to UK & IE residents age 16+. Closes 11.59pm 15.05.2021.
Must have your friend’s consent before tagging them in the comment.
4 winners and the tagged person in each comment will be contacted via Instagram by the official brand’s account: @ghdhair. No other account.
For full terms and conditions & Privacy Policy see: http://ghd.tm/2pVOU0o (link in bio too)
Paid partnership with @ghdhair.
Winners will be announced by @ghdhair.
Prize includes (for winner and tagged person): 10-minute virtual masterclass with @zoesugg & @samantha.cusick, 3 tools from the Hairitage Couture limited-edition
collection (ghd gold, ghd platinum+ and ghd helios)
 
#ghdhairitage #20yearsofghd #ghdwin

Thought I’d share a few snippets of behind the scenes of when I decorated the porch for autumn! Thank you for all the love on my reel by the way, so pleased so many of you loved it and it got you in the autumn spirit! 

Couple of useful things: 
🎃 Pumpkins are AD-Gifted from @tulleyspyopumpkins as well as the hay bales & maize bundles (although I do think you can purchase the maize at the farm as well as the pumpkins and gourds) 
🎃 The doormat was £3.50 from IKEA & I was fully inspired by @thehousethatjenbuilt_ (check out her account) I then used @agoodcom [ad-brand ambassador] paint to decorate! Super easy and SO effective. You can go WILD with any text or pattern! 
🎃 Spiders were from an antique shop, as were the crates! 
🎃 Wreath is around 4/5 years old & I purchased it in @homesense_ukie 
🎃 None of these pumpkins go in the bin! 👍🏼 We use some for soups/pumpkin purée for baking, pass on to friends and family to cook with, decorate at Halloween/pass on to friends, family & neighbours to carve, feed the birds and wildlife & any that don’t get eaten or given away go in our compost bins ready to be used another time on our garden! 👩🏼‍🌾 (one day I’ll attempt to grow my own pumpkins...haha)

node.title: Decorating The Porch : Behind The Scenes 🎃

node.text:
Digital Detox Day Presents: Anxiety  Discussion 3. 

Today’s video is a special one to me, as I'm able to chat and share my wonderful therapist of 6 years with you, Alexis Main. We discuss how social media can trigger anxiety, decrease self-worth and lead us to obsessively craving validation from others.

Rather than constantly comparing ourselves to others online, Alexis offers a range of helpful tips to help lessen the effects of social media induced anxiety and protect ourselves from potentially destructive scrolling habits. 

Remember if you or someone you know if affected by any of the DDDay videos, check my DDD highlight for links to seek help. 

#DigitalDetoxDay #Anxiety #DigitalDetox

node.title: Talking Anxiety With My Therapist 🤯 Digital Detox Day - Discussion 3

Digital Detox Day Presents: Cyberbullying - Discussion 2. 

Today, I chat with Jamie Windust, Chessie King and Katie Snooks and we discuss the prominence of cyberbullying on social media and their own experiences with trolls online.

With over half of adolescents admitting to being both bullied and bullying others online, it’s more important than ever to make social media a kinder, safer place.

#DigitalDetoxDay
#DigitalDetox

Digital Detox Day Presents: Setting Digital Boundaries  Discussion 1. 

In today’s panel discussion, I'm joined by Jordan Stephens, Jamie Laing and Niamh McDade to discuss the importance of setting digital boundaries, especially on social media, to protect our mental health.

By becoming more conscious of how often we’re scrolling through our feeds, we can regain control over our phones and retrain ourselves to “just sit with our thoughts, feelings and moments of stillness” - Zat Rana

node.text:
A little behind the scenes and a few throwbacks to creating the bath bomb with @lush_jack, @markatlush and @Jordanfstephens

If escapism had a smell, this would be it. The scent fills the room, quieting your mind long before you've even dipped your toes in the tub. As IRL dissolves, the colours change from magenta pink to optimistic sky blue and violet, turning the bath water into a swirl of dreamy sunset hues. The perfect concoction of Orange Flower, Neroli, Mimosa, Gardenia & Lavender bring together a floral yet fresh fragrance. For all the times I want to enjoy a beautiful sunset from the comfort of my own bathroom, I'll be reaching for IRL.

All money raised will be going into a one-off fund taking applications for grants from small, grassroots groups who work on mental health issues. If you are one of those, head to Lush website to see how you can apply! 

The bath bomb is limited, once it’s gone it’s gone so head out to your local lush and stock up or place an order online now! It’s going to an incredible cause. 

Available in 19 countries: UK, Ireland, Germany, France, Spain, Portugal, Italy, Sweden, Czech, Hungary, Netherlands, Australia, New Zealand, Belgium, Luxembourg, Korea, Japan & HK 

6 DAYS UNTIL #digitaldetoxday

node.text:
I’m super excited to finally be able to share the campaign we’ve been working on for SOOO long! I present to you : DIGITAL DETOX DAY! With both #Lush & @iamwholeuk (@jordanfstephens) we’ve created this campaign around how social media can affect our mental health and negatively impact our lives.

The world of social media has many benefits, but over the years, it’s become more and more an extension of our hands and minds & we can find ourselves endlessly scrolling, comparing, judging, being cyber bullied, not setting boundaries and not knowing when to switch off. It can be the cause of anxiety, depression, sleeplessness, loneliness and low self esteem and over the years I’ve had thousands of messages from you all, including other creators who are struggling with how social media makes them feel, so this felt like the perfect campaign to put together. 

Over the next week, we’ll be sharing content here and over on @iamwholeuk on many of the topics linked with mental health and the digital world with some incredible panelists and fellow creators, friends and even my therapist! 

On Saturday 5th September we’ll be asking anyone and everyone (that’s you reading this) to switch off for mental health. A whole digital detox day where we put our devices down and re-connect and re-evaluate how social media makes us feel.

We hope this week of content helps those of you who need it and ultimately we hope we can encourage you to find a way to have a better relationship with your device and improve your mental wellbeing.

I’ve also worked closely with Lush to create a limited edition bath bomb “IRL” with money going into a one-off fund taking applications for grants from small, grassroots groups who work on mental health issues. Those are available in store and online NOW! (There will be a making of going live tomorrow). #digitaldetoxday

node.text:
SO SO excited to share the cover of “The Magpie Society - Two For Joy” that both @amymccullochbooks & I poured our heart and souls into through lockdown 🙌🏼 I can’t wait for you to read the next instalment & find out a bit more about what Audrey & Ivy discover next (sorry for the cliffhanger ending, you don’t have to wait much longer 😜) Out on November 25th and available to pre order NOW!!! 🙌🏼 

I’ve linked where you can pre order signed copies in my stories & in the linktree in my bio for every link available (including the signed ones if you find that easier than stories or stories have gone once you read this) 

It’s been so lovely reading your reviews and seeing you sharing the love for “one for sorrow” & we are equally grateful for every share & pre order this time around too, so thank you thank you thank you 🥰 It wasn’t easy writing this through my first trimester & a strict lockdown let me tell you 😅 As always it’s been a bloody pleasure getting to write alongside my friend Amy who was SO patient with me when I had days of “Amy I can’t even open my laptop” 😂😂 

Let me know in the comments if you’ve pre ordered! 💕💕

We decided to do the party pretty last minute and we were struggling to find some local businesses to make it come together (which obviously makes sense considering all the weddings/hens/parties that have been postponed because of covid now going ahead) so we weren’t too hopeful! I asked on stories if any businesses had availability or any cancellations or if any of you could recommend anything and we found some absolute GEMS that I really wanted to share! 
 
(FYI we paid every single business in full, nothing was gifted & they didn’t ask us to share but I love discovering amazing businesses so wanted to do the same) 

🎂 was provided by Kate at  @skymeadowbakery and let me tell you, it was so delicious! The icing was so light & the cake was so fluffy. I heard multiple people say that the chocolate cake was the best they’d ever eaten! 

🕯 styling & tables were by Leah at @bohoandbloomprophire who totally got my vision & dressed the tent so beautifully! I loved the low tables (even when I needed help to get up haha) 

🍹 the bar and cocktails were by @thedrunkenjockeys and they were amazing!! We had a good mixture of cocktails and mocktails & they were all phenomenal. The guys were also so great & lovely! 💕 

🧀 Grazing table was supplied by our trusted fave Katie at @stylisheatsuk who always absolutely nails it! Everyone nibbled away happily all afternoon. 

⛺️ The stretch tent & lights were from @tentstyleuk & again we’ve used these guys before and they are so great!! 

If there’s anything else you can spot & want to know where it’s from, let me know! 🙌🏼 
All these wonderful companies made the day so special & with such short notice too!
